#: ../../G/gender-mender.rst:5
msgid "gender mender"
msgstr "gender mender"

#: ../../G/gender-mender.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../G/gender-mender.rst:9
msgid ""
"[common] A cable connector shell with either two male or two female "
"connectors on it, used to correct the mismatches that result when some "
":ref:`loser` didn't understand the RS232C specification and the distinction "
"between DTE and DCE. Used esp. for RS-232C parts in either the original D-25"
" or the IBM PC's bogus D-9 format. Also called gender bender, gender "
"blender, sex changer, and even homosexual adapter; however, there appears to"
" be some confusion as to whether a male homosexual adapter has pins on both "
"sides (is doubly male) or sockets on both sides (connects two males)."
msgstr ""
"[一般的] 二つのオス、または二つのメスのコネクタが付いたケーブルのコネクタシェル。どこかの\\ :ref:`loser`\\ "
"がRS232C仕様とDTE・DCEの区別を理解していなかったために生じる不整合を直すために使われる。特に、元のD-25形式かIBM "
"PCのいかさまなD-9形式のRS-232C部品に使われる。gender bender、gender blender、sex "
"changer、さらにはhomosexual adapterとも呼ばれる。ただし、オスのhomosexual "
"adapterが両側にピンがあるのか(二重にオス)、両側にソケットがあるのか(二つのオスをつなぐ)については、いくらか混乱があるようだ。"
